<P><H1 align=center>CUSTOMER DETAILS – CR020</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P><H3>Surname, Forenames, Title: </H3>these basic customer 
details must be completed to proceed further. If ‘Other’ is selected from the 
title drop-down, a field will appear to the right of the list, where the title 
must be entered
<P></P>
<P><H3>Date of Birth: </H3>this must be completed, and must be 
in the correct format – dd/mm/yyyy. If the format is incorrect, an error message 
will be displayed. When the date of birth has been entered, the age will be 
calculated and displayed in the ‘Age’ field.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Sex: </H3>if the title is entered as ‘Mr’, ‘Mrs’, 
‘Miss’ or ‘Ms’, the relevant sex will automatically be selected from the 
drop-down list. If ‘Dr’ or ‘Other’ are selected, select ‘Male’ or ‘Female’ from 
the list
<P></P>
<P><H3>Address: </H3>this is not mandatory at this stage, 
however it will need to be captured if the customer wishes to proceed further, 
past the quotation stage. To find the address using PAF Search, enter the 
postcode and click ‘PAF Search’. This will bring up a list of addresses that 
share the postcode entered. Select the correct one, and the address details will 
populate the fields. Alternatively you may enter the property number (if known) 
and the postcode before clicking on the PAF Search. If the address is found by 
the search, the address fields will be populated immediately.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Contact Details: </H3>select the contact type from the 
dropdown list (eg. home, work, mobile), and enter the number and contact time, 
and select which is the preferred contact.
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>this leads to the next screen.
<P></P>

